Dear Mr. Cirillo,

My name is Dylan Montgomery. I am a student entrepreneur working on technology related to local farmers, regional food systems, and food-access infrastructure in Northeast Ohio.

I am reaching out because your role in corporate communications stood out to me. Much of the work I am doing involves not only the technical side of coordinating local agricultural systems, but also the challenge of communicating those ideas in a way that is clear, credible, and capable of moving people to pay attention and act.

I have been especially interested in how organizations frame regional efforts in ways that connect institutional priorities, public understanding, and practical action. Given your background in external communications and media relations, I would value the chance to hear your perspective on that problem, particularly how narratives are shaped so they resonate beyond the immediate technical details.

If you would be open to a brief conversation, I would greatly appreciate it. Even a short discussion would be valuable.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Best,
Dylan Montgomery

--_000_CH3PPF55EB0412064CA3F7F846A2AB3A392F4582CH3PPF55EB04120_
